freetext.SYMPTOMS_DESCRIPTION: Ive had intermittent soreness in the arm where I got the vaccine.

freetext.SYSTEMIC_REACTION_OTHER: Mildly tender nodes just above the elbow, anteromedial aspect, with additional small nodules palpable extending upward from there. This is on the arm that received the vaccine.
Some aching in the joints of my hands and my knees. Symptoms resolved by early afternoon

Tender nodes just above my elbow (anteromedial aspect) of left arm. I also have what feels like a chain of small, tender bumps extending up my arm from the larger nodes at my elbow. This is the arm where I was given the vaccine.
